Count incoming TCP SYNs per source IP in a sliding window (LRU hash map keyed by src IP). If a source exceeds N SYNs/second, start dropping its SYNs for a cooldown period. Teaches: LRU maps, time-based logic with bpf_ktime_get_ns, and the difference between stateless and stateful filtering. The interesting failure mode is handling IP spoofing — which leads naturally to SYN cookies 
